README:

File is split into 4 segments bugs/WIP, dependancies, parameters, script flow, folder structure, file formats & naming convention

* Genomes are deleted after transcripts are extracted (to save space)
* Only transcripts which are experimentally are selected from the reference species

Reference species genomes:

Xenopus tropicalis : Xenbase - v10 (genome), v9-10lift (annotation)
Xenopus laevis : Xenbase - v9.2(genome & anno)
Danio rerio : Ensembl - GRCz11 (genome & anno)

Bugs:


Dependancies:

GNU Parallel/parasllel_script.sh	(>=20200922)
File::Temp (perl-cpan)
extract_transcript_regions.sh (https://github.com/stephenfloor/extract-transcript-regions)
Python		(>=2.7.16)
R		(>=4.0.2)
bedtools	(>=2.29.2)

Parameters:

script(in/to) - program - params - comment
do_blast.sh(in) - tblastx - { -word_size 5 -outfmt 11 -evalue 0.01 } - Overall BLAST


WIP:

all-toall tBLASTx (all2alltblastx.sh)
Trim gene-names only in extract_genomic_regions.sh

Script Flow:

START the pipeline: run_pipeline_ensembl.sh - the script takes only one parameter - file containing the gene list 

 qsub run_pipeline_ensembl.sh files/genelist.txt 

Folder structure, file formats & naming convention:

all-all tblastx: $gene.$query.$subject
